# SEO Page Rules

Every public-facing `page.tsx` in the `app/` directory must follow these conventions.

## Required Exports

1. **`generateMetadata`** (or static `metadata`) must be exported.
2. Metadata must include a **canonical URL** via `alternates.canonical`.
3. Metadata must include **Open Graph** tags (`title`, `description`, `url`, `siteName`).

## Use the SEO Utility Layer

- Import `buildPageMetadata` from `@/lib/seo` for detail pages.
- Import `buildListingMetadata` from `@/lib/seo` for category/listing pages.
- Do NOT hardcode `https://clip.art` in metadata — use the `path` parameter and let the builder construct the full URL.
- Do NOT manually interpolate title suffixes like `| clip.art` — the builder handles this.

## Title Rules

- Titles must be under 60 characters.
- Use `buildTitle()` (called internally by `buildPageMetadata`) to avoid the "Free Free" duplication bug.
- Pattern: `{Subject} — Free {Category} {ContentType Label} | clip.art`

## JSON-LD Structured Data

- Image detail pages: include `ImageObject` + `BreadcrumbList` via `buildImageJsonLd()` and `buildDetailBreadcrumb()` from `@/lib/seo-jsonld`.
- `buildImageJsonLd` must receive `datePublished`, `width`, `height`. `encodingFormat` defaults to `image/webp`.
- Video/learn pages: include `VideoObject` via `buildVideoJsonLd()` — only include optional fields when they have values.

## H1 Tag

- Every public page must render exactly one `<h1>` tag.
- The `<h1>` must be in the initial server-rendered HTML (not behind client-side state).

## Detail Page Requirements

- The main content area must be wrapped in an `<article>` element.
- Hero images must use the `unoptimized` prop (R2-served, no Next.js optimization needed).
- Tags must be rendered as `<Link>` elements pointing to `/search?q={tag}&content_type={variant}`.
- Related image alt text must include content type context (e.g. "— free clip art").
- Related image `href` must use `img.category` directly from the DB row, not `getCategorySlugForImage`.
- Pass `created_at` from the DB row to the image object for JSON-LD `datePublished`.
- Pass parent category `seo_content` to the detail component for contextual richness.
- Include a "More in this style" cross-link section when the image has a style tag.
- Descriptions generated by `classifyPrompt` must be 150-300 chars (2-3 sentences, unique, not echoing the prompt).

## Sitemap

- After creating a new public page, add it to `app/sitemap.ts`.
- Category/hub pages: priority 0.9-0.95.
- Detail pages (images, coloring, illustrations): priority 0.5.
- Pack detail pages: priority 0.8.

## Content Type Paths

When setting the `path` parameter:
- Clip art: `{category}/{slug}`
- Coloring: `coloring-pages/{theme}/{slug}`
- Illustrations: `illustrations/{category}/{slug}`
- Worksheets: `worksheets/{grade}/{subject}/{topic}/{slug}`
- Learn: `learn/{slug}`

## Worksheet URL Pattern

Worksheets are the only content type with a 4-level URL hierarchy (grade → subject → topic → slug). When building worksheet pages:

- Landing: `/worksheets` — priority 0.95 in sitemap.
- Grade hub: `/worksheets/{grade}` — priority 0.9.
- Subject hub: `/worksheets/{grade}/{subject}` — priority 0.9.
- Topic hub: `/worksheets/{grade}/{subject}/{topic}` — priority 0.85.
- Detail: `/worksheets/{grade}/{subject}/{topic}/{slug}` — priority 0.5.
- Category slugs encode the hierarchy with `--` separators: `1st-grade--math--addition`.
- Use `worksheetDetailPath()` from `@/lib/seo` for detail paths; use `categoryPath("worksheet", "grade/subject")` for hub paths.
- JSON-LD `BreadcrumbList` must include all 4 hub levels plus Home.
- Detail pages must render as PDF downloads (aspect 3:4), not PNG.
